10 Shia worshippers killed in Balochistan suicide attack
At least 10 Shias were killed and 10 others wounded when a suicide bomber struck an imambargah in Bagh tehsil of Kachhi district, 300 kilometres off Quetta in Balochistan. Tehsildar Bagh Ahsan Ali Gulla confirmed the death toll, saying the suicide attacker exploded during evening prayers.
This is a developing story and will be updated accordingly